OL,3,CRE provision in NI to be reviewed
OL,5,FThe Department of Education has
OL,6,Fannounced the first revision of the
OL,7,Freligious education syllabus in
OL,8,FNorthern Ireland in nearly 20 years.
OL,10,FThe curriculum is to include more
OL,11,Fabout other religions, alongside
OL,12,FChristianity, but there will be no
OL,13,Fchange to how collective worship is
OL,14,Fcurrently delivered.
OL,16,FProvision is to be reviewed by an
OL,17,Findependent panel.
OL,19,FHowever Education Minister Paul Givan
OL,20,Fsaid Christianity will "remain central
OL,21,Fto the syllabus".
